### What are the conditions for retiring troops?

Abdulle Abella Sulov(Abdujalil Abdurasulov)Report from Kiev, Ukraine

The negotiations continued for a whole day, and the result was that Porigo agreed to ease the situation that night.

Be Belarus President Lukashenko is a close ally of Putin. He talks with Pleigo on Saturday.

As a part of the transaction, Porigerin has been allowed to go to Belarus, and the Kremlin said he would revoke all his allegations to him.

Lukashenko's news office said the negotiation was under the consent of Putin.

As part of the agreement, the Kremlin agreed to revoke his prosecution against the leaders of the Wagner Group, and also provided security guarantees to the Wagner soldiers.

Since the beginning of the invasion, Russia has been using Belarusian territory to attack Ukraine, which has effectively harmed Belarus's sovereignty.

The weakening of Putin's control of power has threatened Minsk's Lukashenko regime, which seriously depends on Moscow.

Putin News Secretary Dimitri Peskov said that Wagner's mercenaries can sign the Ministry of Defense Contract, and soldiers participating in the rebellion will not be prosecuted.

