### Is this the ending of the Pryopin and Wagner Group?

A expert told Broadcasting Corporation that Porigerjin moved to Belarus, and the Wagner soldiers were absorbed to the Russian army, which may mean the end of this infamous mercenary organization.

Andrew D'Anieri, headquartered in the American Think Tank Atlantic Council, said the information from Russia was chaotic and unclear, and it was difficult to say what would happen in the end.

But he also said that Wagner's retreat did not mean that all private military companies in Russia were "out".

"Even if they are illegal in Russia in the strict sense, in the past year, we have seen the surge in such organizations."

![](Images/BBC Chinese/2023-06-25T10-16-13.000Z/_129015688_capture.png)Image source, reuters

