These seemingly major breakthroughs -have not been published in journals that have been reviewed by peer -aim to understand infertility, miscarriage and birth defects. But they also caused moral and legal concerns. The scientific community, as well as a wider society, now need to consider the artificial embryo trained by these laboratories -essentially how close to the real human embryo. Putting public discussions, coupled with updating regulations and considering how to commercialize such research, it will encourage the public to support the transformation of valuable research that may be transformed into treatment methods.

