After completing the fertilization, the fertilized eggs will be split for about 4 days, and then contracted into blastocyst. After that, the blastocyst was bed in the uterus, which marked the beginning of pregnancy. On the 14th day, the embryo experienced "the formation of the original bowel". At this time, the prototype of the body began to form, and different cell lines appeared. One of the characteristics is "primitive stripes", which occurs when symmetrically developed on both sides.

Generally speaking, in the United Kingdom and many other countries, the cultivation of human embryo cannot be cultivated for more than 14 days. This means that what happened after -, including how embryos organize themselves into different types of organizations -the exact scientific details of the other types are still a mystery. Researchers can cultivate more longer for animal embryos, but have limited correlation.

